formattedAddress: Food Garden, Asia Square (12 Marina View)

tips.text: Love their create your own meal and $9.90 is pretty good for CBD pricing. Chicken is tender and flavourful! Eating healthy ain't so tough afterall!
Tasty breast meat along with healthy sides
Really nice drinks. Try the kingfish sashimi and the fantastic bahru boot leg. Sit at the bar because the staff is really nice!
Fabulicious as always, with a special birthday cake some more... Yummmm
Classy and romantic setting, good for a date. Food is not too bad a bit expensive for what you get. Steak was ok, truffle fries were pretty good.
I always take the $15 set with Chirashi don. So superb! Their marketing and interior efforts are pretty weak, but their soba is awesome! Hope more people visit to support! I always love good soba 😋

formattedAddress: 2 Duxton Hill, #01-01 (cnr Duxton Rd & Duxton Hill)

tips.text: Quite enjoyed the Earl Grey Choco. A nice, light dessert with nice hints of earl grey, chocolate and sliced banana in the middle.
Very reasonable organic meals! Om mani padme om!
Generally good food and drinks. Great ambience too. Love the grilled corn on the cob and the blue corn cake dessert.
order the northern stuff, obviously - good homestyle cooking. 地三鮮，醬茄子，酸菜粉絲，涼拌腐皮絲，東北拉皮 are all excellent and filling.

venue.name: Song Fa Bak Kut Teh 松发肉骨茶

tips.text: One of the Best Bah Kut Teh,imo. I totally love their soup, and side dishes of deepfried doughsticks, peanuts & salted veggies! I've considered this as a gem among my fav foodhunts in town! :)
Dark chocolate banana is SUPER AWESOME!!! Choc is rich yet not too sweet or creamy, banana taste real. On softer side, tofu strawberry is more mild, combi of sour, sweet n smooth!
Must try the salt baked beetroot, w burrata & truffle honey, mini Spanish breakfast, and popcorn milk chocolate mousse! The short ribs and scallops were just okay. Arrive post 930 to avoid the wait.
Great view of the Marina Bay Sands. Nice open view at the upstairs bar.

venue.name: Chinatown Food Street (牛車水美食街)

tips.text: Newly renovated Chinatown food street is wider, cleaner, has more stalls offering different foods including Indian food and satays, BBQ chicken and is covered by a massive glass and steel roof
It's very good (I wouldn't call it "amazingly good") but I still prefer my Adam Road NL.
Plenty of good food at reasonable prices.

formattedAddress: #B1-44 Clarke Quay Central (6 Eu Tong Sen Street)

tips.text: Cauliflower veggie burger, simple and tasty! Sweet potatoe fries were really good barely any grease
From kaiseiki, they have changed to a la carte japanese restaurant. Quality of food is still stand out. Sashimi platter was pure joy to eat, grilled onigiri had homemade taste & somen was refreshing.

formattedAddress: The Fullerton Bay Hotel Singapore (80 Collyer Quay)

tips.text: Their salad buffet is $29 but if u wanna add meat from the carving station (roast ribeye) u pay $36. Worth the price for food and ambience!!
Expensive 12 dollars for a salad) but fresh and tasty. Caesar was excellent
Tuna belly was so fresh and good! The rice was done to perfection. I strongly suspect the wasabi here is the real authentic one (ie. not horseradish), it brings a sweet after taste.
Absolutely delicious  !! Had the Black spicy tonkotsu special.  Ramen had perfect texture, eggs were nice and gooey in the middle, broth was tasty.  Even better with ground sesame.
WiFi pass: "ilovemellower"

venue.name: Tong Heng Confectionery 東興餅家

tips.text: almond paste is nice... good for lungs and skin   ;-)
The Yangnyum flavor is awesome! KFC is definitely not comparable!
great place for brunch, desserts & a working lunch. staff keep on their smiley attitude even during a full house. never fails.

venue.name: Outram Park Fried Kway Teow Mee

tips.text: Note: The queue at peak hours goes round the side and behind the stall. So don't be too happy when you see "no / short queue" in front of the stall.
Nice hangout place located in d CBD area.... :)
The strawberry mochi fish is sooooo nice !! In love with it

BE Sanger (pulled pork, chipotle aioli - served in brioche bun): Ask 2 cut 'burger' in half- makes for a nice snack to share over cocktails. Aioli gave ea bite a mild play w d chilli & garlic flavours

formattedAddress: #01-58, Amoy Street Food Centre, 7 Maxwell Road
location.address: #01-58, Amoy Street Food Centre, 7 Maxwell Road

tips.text: the food here packs a punch! spicy shiok
Great open air views of Boat Quay. Cocktails are not too bad, the Cuba cocktail slips down very nicely.
Authentic Korean food! Two thumbs up.

formattedAddress: 2 Teck Lim Road (Off Keong Saik Rd)

tips.text: Good value set lunch. Yummy food with even yummier desserts. Don't miss their lemon tart - One of those rare places that dares to let the tartness shines through. Love!
From the folks who brought you Ronin and The Plain; try the drumlets, the fish & chips and the off menu desserts. Just 5 days old but steady showing so much potential. The coffee is also exemplary.
Been here since I was a kid, gotta try the dai ha mai

venue.name: Lan Zhou La Mian  蘭州拉麵

tips.text: They have the most amazing fried Hokkien mee! Must try! Patronise them and keep the place alive!
The spicy fragrant flavour is the best, but you need to be able to handle your szechuan peppers
Superb Italian fare
Save some space for the Pistachio Tiramisu! Much better than the Lava Cake.
Tasty and good value omakase if you don't mind early 6pm seating. Will be back.
Not hard to find!
Food is totally overpriced but drinks and atmosphere at bar upstairs are great, so have dinner somewhere else and come here only for drinks.
The prawn & asparagus is a nightmarish mix of frighteningly stale prawns & dead asparagus.
Calamari: If u think this is u typical deep-fried version, consider again. It is really char-grilled (4 a change) & surprisingly tasty. Recommended!
The seasoned meat are tasty as compared to the grilled ones. They used traditional charcoal for barbecuing.
I love the crispy seaweed appetizer!
Great night. Stunning views, great beers, fantastic food. Better than the hype suggests.
